    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered for the discerning collector is a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six powerplant with individual throttle bodies. This specimen retains its original factory-spec 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox and M-Variable Differential Lock. Mechanically impeccable, the VANOS system has been proactively serviced, and the rear subframe has undergone professional reinforcement to ensure structural rigidity. The high-revving naturally aspirated engine delivers linear power delivery across the entire RPM range, complemented by a pristine chassis with original-spec suspension geometry. Zero fluid leaks, no dash lights, and a flawless interior make this an investment-grade example of Bavarian engineering at its zenith.",
